danbooru-ruby-grabber is a danbooru downloader â€” simple script for download images from danbooru.donmai.us, konachan.com, e621.net, behoimi.org and yande.re. Support of any danbooru-powered site can be added easily.

Usage: danbooru.rb [options] "tags"
    -k, --konachan                   Download from konachan.com instead of danbooru.donmai.us
    -e, --e621                       Download from e621.net instead of danbooru.donmai.us
    -b, --behoimi                    Download from behoimi.org instead of danbooru.donmai.us
    -y, --yandere                    Download from yande.re instead of danbooru.donmai.us
    -w, --wget                       Use wget for download
    -c, --curl                       Use curl for download
    -s, --storage DIR                Storage mode (all images in one dir and symlinks in tagged dirs)
    -u, --user USERNAME              Username
    -p, --password PASSWORD          Password

You can use up to 2 tags with basic account. Images are stored in tag-named directory. Also script creates file named files.bbs with all tags of each image.

You need nokogiri to be installed. You can install it by this command:

gem install nokogiri
Note: may be you need to use sudo.

Have fun.

